animal.description: This sweet affectionate boy seeks a quiet adult home where he will get lots of cuddles with his human! Sam lives to love and be loved -- and will be your Right Hand Man and Best Friend. His whole being revolves around his humans. We would like him to be the only dog, so he is spoiled. He is 3 /12 years old and about 65 pounds. For playmates, he seems to get along best with alpha females! Hmmm, likes being told what to do and when/how to do it? Sam would LOVE a yard with dog door, so he can freely go in and out. Dislikes being crated or tethered. He is quiet and happy in the car (moving or not, company or not), or at the office (just his 2 people there). He enjoys daily walks, but must be on leash because of hip dysplasia. If up to him, he would run hard and then be uncomfortable later. His humans satisfy his need for action, with lots of mental exercises: hide and seek, finding hidden toys/treats, playing games. His ideal home would be out of the snow easier to get out and about and romp around, in Winter. Sam gets uneasy with new folks coming in, so proper introduction is a must. Easy to do, once you know his quirks. He takes his job seriously as a Protector of his loved ones. He has been working with a trainer and showing great progress. Continued training would really benefit this boy. He really does want to please. Very treat motivated! But, have to be careful to not be over indulgent. Important for him to keep a svelte physique for less stress on his hips, AND to attract the girls!. Typical birddog, he has some prey drive, so please no cats or chickens! And, please, no kids. Little ones make him nervous (me too, Sam!). Do consider this Darling Boy, for a spot in your heart and home. If you are interested in Sam, please fill out an adoption application online at www.tahoewarf.com. and contact Robyn at robyn.orloff@icloud.com

animal.description:
Rocky is an Aidi. He is a North African dog breed used as a livestock guardian, protecting herds of sheep and goats. 

That being said... he is just that. He will be your Guardian, your champion, and your protector if you let him. 

Rocky needs a very strong Alpha owner. He needs rules, structure, and boundaries set in place. He shouldn’t be babied. Pampered, kissed, pet, brushed, and loved of course... but he doesn’t like to be spoken too like he is a child because he’s too smart for that. 

Once Rocky sees you as his confident friend, he melts like butter. He will do trust falls and give endless kisses and cuddles.  He loves to play outside with the hose. HE ADORES you completely. Absolutely no small children for Rocky as he was severely abused by them. If children visit he must be put away. 
Any size dog or cat of any kind Rocky will do great with. He loves other animals... he even likes lizards.  
He will do best in a quiet household with out a ton of visitors. 

Rocky came to PUP when another rescue was having trouble figuring out why he wouldn’t listen. Turns out rocky speaks French! He’s learning English well. peut-il venir vivre avec vous?

If your interested in meeting Rocky please set up an appointment with Paws unite people in East Patchogue by sending us a message.
Our cats and dogs are at our Rehabilitation Center in East Patchogue, NY or in private foster homes. They are available to see by appointment. Email Adoptions@pawsunitepeople.com for more information.¿
Our cats and dogs are not available to be adopted out of state via a transporter. All of our animals require meet and greets, we do home visits and reference checks. If you are willing to travel to meet the pet and live out of area, feel free to inquire, but we will not send any animal to a home sight unseen.

animal.description:
Hi ya'll it's me Mick. i've been moving around a bit so i thought i would check in with you! I'm still looking for my forever home. I'm 5 years old but i have a lot of life left in me. I don't want to spend the rest of my life in a cage. My story is sad, I was on the euthanasia list at the shelter, got adopted but it was an apartment and not the right fit, so I went back to the shelter. Than this cool trainer saved me and I fell in love with him. Well he lost his place to live, so I than went to boarding. And than someone wanted to adopt me. I was so happy, but he slept 12-14 hours a day and was kenneling me at that time, I don't like kennels much, don't need one. He tried to grab me even after i growled at him, and i bit him, i'm sorry but he didn't listen to my warning and I didn't know what else to do. MY friends say they have NEVER SEEN ME BE AGGRESIVE. I am always a happy wiggle butt. I love walks, and to play. I have house manners, and I even like calm dogs. And even smaller dogs. Well now I'm back in boarding looking for that perfect home. The perfect home for me would be a quiet calm home with a backyard and someone to love me, that would walk me and not crate me. Maybe an experienced handler. I am an awesome dog waiting for you. Please call 520-800-4633 asap and ask for DDee to meet me. I promise I will be a good boy!MEET >>Mick DDee>!! **Please Note: This is a courtesy post for another rescue; different adoption fees/policy apply.

animal.description:
UPDATE: DEC 2020 - Danny's adoption fell thru, he is still available and will be best as an only dog, no children. Teddy/Teddie, our senior, had knee surgery, recovering well, and has an adoption pending. Henri has an ADOPTION PENDING!

UPDATE: NOV 2020 - Rue has been ADOPTED! Danny has an ADOPTION PENDING! 

UPDATE: OCT 2020 - We were finally able to bring in TWO Spitz from S. Korea that have been waiting since FEB 2020! Danny & Rue, both young adult males, have just arrived, and are being given time to chill, as well as have vet check-ups. Danny is a white Spitz about 4 years old and Rue has a "wolf" colored coat and is also a Spitz. Each boy will be listed under our Chicagoland Eskie Rescue listings, we do need time to get new photos! Thanks again for your patience!

UPDATE: AUGUST 2020 - We are just starting to get a couple of new Eskies into the rescue. Transportation is still difficult, United Airlines Pet Safe Program continues to have cargo "suspended" for flying dogs/pets. As we get in new dogs, we will get them listed as promptly as possible. Please be patient, as there are many who have been waiting throughout the pandemic period....aka we do have a waiting list!

UPDATE: July 2020 - Due to COVID-19, we are still having significant difficulty transporting dogs. We normally rescue Eskies from a variety of locations and use the United Pet Safe program to fly dogs from the west coast and southern states to Chicago, but their program has been suspended for several months now. International transportation of dogs has also been suspended until further notice from South Korea. We are terribly sorry for any disappointment this wait has caused. As soon as we are able to bring in more Eskies we will get them listed! Thanks so much for your patience during this trying time.

Due to the threat of COVID-19, the 'stay-at-home' orders in the state of IL, social distancing, and only essential businesses being open, it has been challenging to conduct adoptions as usually. We are a foster home based rescue and do not have a facility. We depend on space at our vet clinic and our own homes to introduce our dogs to potential adopters, and then the homes of adopters to meet again to go over vet care paperwork and our adoption contract. In the current status of our country, you can see how this has become difficult. Now that the weather is better, we are starting to meet applicants outside to keep social distancing easy. Please have patience as we "reinvent the wheel" to figure out new plans to move forward, and still keep our mission statement as our goal!

Chicagoland Eskie Rescue has a NEW website! ALL of our available dogs will be listed on Petfinder and can be found thru our website! Simply go to: www.chicagolandekierescue.com and find the button for available dogs, which will in turn bring you back to Petfinder to all of our listed dogs. Our new website will also feature an ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION!! YIPPY! Applications will be available to fill out online, so no more waiting, emailing, responding, etc. HAPPY DANCE! This has been a long time coming, websites cost money, all of our monies have always gone directly to the dogs. Fortunately, we have received donations specifically to help us launch a new website! So exciting! THANK YOU for your patience!

animal.description:
Rosie is in temp foster right now. But, needs a permanent home. She needs a home with a strong experienced handler.

What can I say?  Rosie is full of sass. She is very well behaved most of the time.  She is housebroken and is completely vetted.  

Rosie is currently in foster in Indianapolis. She is a great baby!! She is great with kids ages 7 and up.  VERY PLAYFUL!  Loves Rope, Ball, and walks.  She walks wonderfully on a harness as well.  

She wants a furever home so badly.  She is the victim of divorce.  So, this is in no way any fault of her own. Needs experienced foster or adopter. MUST be only pet in home. No exceptions.

She is the epitome of the perfect gal.

animal.description:
Riley is a 12 yo, 22 lb hairless mix. Yep, he is mostly naked of fur. He has a little strip of fur down his back but the underside is smooth and hairless. Riley is an energetic guy who loves to play a good game of fetch--then snuggle under blankets and nap.  Riley will nudge you with his snout when he's ready for play, or attention. Consider adding this special guy to your family. Apply today at ABTR.org.

All our rescues have been fully vetted, tested Heartworm negative, current on all shots and spayed or neutered, unless age or health prohibits. They are fostered in AL, GA, or MS. 

ADOPTION FEES: 
Six months and under - $450 
Six to Twelve months - $400  
One to Two years - $350 
Two years and Older - $300 
 
 Mixes, designer breeds and other breed fees may vary.

To adopt or make a donation, please visit www.abtr.org.
